-Hmm. What could it be?
-What could it be? Whoa.

786
00:44:41.431 --> 00:44:44.226
Now. I have two whole suits.

787
00:44:44.309 --> 00:44:46.228
You're spoiling me rotten.
-You're already rotten.

788
00:44:46.311 --> 00:44:48.355
Thank you.
Hey. Sammy.

789
00:44:48.438 --> 00:44:51.024
-Sammy. look.
-Check out dad's new duds.

790
00:44:51.316 --> 00:44:54.736
Hey. I thought
we agreed to not give him that.

791
00:44:54.819 --> 00:44:57.030
Blame Santa. He got it for him.

792
00:44:57.781 --> 00:44:59.741
These things
they're saying about you.

793
00:44:59.824 --> 00:45:01.201
hmm. they're not right.

794
00:45:01.284 --> 00:45:03.662
Pop. relax. okay?

795
00:45:03.745 --> 00:45:05.622
Bob Motta's telegram
made it very clear

796
00:45:05.705 --> 00:45:07.040
that he's coming aboard.

797
00:45:07.123 --> 00:45:09.418
That means we're gonna
divide the ruin evenly. 50/50.

798
00:45:09.501 --> 00:45:10.627
Why'd he say yes?

799
00:45:10.710 --> 00:45:12.754
Saw my speech
on the evening news.

800
00:45:12.837 --> 00:45:13.880
Knocked his socks off.

801
00:45:13.963 --> 00:45:15.716
Said he had to be a part of it.

802
00:45:15.799 --> 00:45:18.510
It was a good speech. right?

803
00:45:18.718 --> 00:45:20.345
I haven't seen it.

804
00:45:22.681 --> 00:45:24.182
Gonna get a fresh one.

805
00:45:26.184 --> 00:45:29.146
Oh. yeah. I know.
It was a big surprise...

806
00:45:33.400 --> 00:45:36.361
And how do you
know this fella. this Bob?

807
00:45:36.444 --> 00:45:39.114
I know him
from my first year as a P.D.

808
00:45:39.197 --> 00:45:41.742
Salt of the earth. no nonsense.

809
00:45:41.825 --> 00:45:44.202
He's gonna be a great
addition to the team.

810
00:45:44.744 --> 00:45:46.454
Why you doing this?

811
00:45:47.706 --> 00:45:49.249
I have to.

812
00:45:50.375 --> 00:45:52.169
You want to.

813
00:45:52.252 --> 00:45:54.171
Even if it puts
your life in danger?

814
00:45:54.254 --> 00:45:55.422
-Stop.
-Even if it puts

815
00:45:55.505 --> 00:45:57.257
your family's life in danger?
-Don't do that.

816
00:45:59.509 --> 00:46:01.136
Drunk Uncle Tod. Perfect timing.

817
00:46:04.681 --> 00:46:06.808
Hello.

818
00:46:06.891 --> 00:46:08.768
Merry Christmas. Sam.

819
00:46:10.395 --> 00:46:11.480
John?

820
00:46:12.689 --> 00:46:15.025
Sure hope
I didn't ruin the holiday.

821
00:46:15.108 --> 00:46:17.068
I heard about
your old man's car.

822
00:46:18.236 --> 00:46:19.529
How'd you hear about that?

823
00:46:19.612 --> 00:46:22.199
Oh. Some cops
were laughing about it.

824
00:46:22.282 --> 00:46:24.534
Is he there? Can I speak to him?

825
00:46:24.617 --> 00:46:25.744
Who?

826
00:46:26.494 --> 00:46:27.829
Your dad.

827
00:46:32.125 --> 00:46:34.253
Yeah. I don't think
that's a very good idea. John.

828
00:46:34.336 --> 00:46:36.713
Oh. come on. Sam.
I just wanna say I'm sorry.

829
00:46:37.255 --> 00:46:40.258
Mom would be ashamed of me
if I didn't do it personally.

830
00:46:43.511 --> 00:46:45.472
Yeah. you know what?

831
00:46:45.555 --> 00:46:46.598
Here he is.

832
00:46:48.433 --> 00:46:49.642
Hey. pop.

833
00:46:51.311 --> 00:46:53.188
John Gacy wants to talk to you.

834
00:46:55.273 --> 00:46:57.442
-Hmm.
-Hmm.

835
00:47:02.155 --> 00:47:03.156
No.

836
00:47:03.531 --> 00:47:05.158
He asked for you.

837
00:47:13.416 --> 00:47:14.626
Hello?

838
00:47:14.709 --> 00:47:17.837
Mr. Amirante.
It's John Gacy.

839
00:47:18.505 --> 00:47:20.507
When I heard
about what happened. sir.

840
00:47:20.590 --> 00:47:22.467
I just had to call. See...

841
00:47:22.801 --> 00:47:25.553
I lost my own dad on Christmas.

842
00:47:27.639 --> 00:47:29.641
Never could do right by him.

843
00:47:29.974 --> 00:47:32.686
But he was my pop
and I loved him.

844
00:47:32.769 --> 00:47:35.772
And Christmas hasn't
been the same since he's gone.

845
00:47:39.401 --> 00:47:40.444
All right.

846
00:47:40.527 --> 00:47:42.821
Uh. well. anyway...

847
00:47:42.904 --> 00:47:45.449
I just had to say I'm sorry that
some jerks vandalized your car

848
00:47:45.532 --> 00:47:47.576
just because
your son's my lawyer.

849
00:47:47.659 --> 00:47:51.287
You know. there are
a lot of nuts out there.

850
00:48:22.569 --> 00:48:24.487
He wasn't like that.

851
00:48:26.656 --> 00:48:28.784
Not like what they're saying.
Like those other boys.

852
00:48:28.867 --> 00:48:31.536
He wasn't like that.
-We know. mom.

853
00:48:32.829 --> 00:48:35.165
He was kind and smart.

854
00:48:35.248 --> 00:48:36.208
Liz.

855
00:48:36.291 --> 00:48:38.752
He would have done something.

856
00:48:38.835 --> 00:48:40.879
God. he would've done something.

857
00:48:49.554 --> 00:48:51.473
I wanna say something.

858
00:48:52.515 --> 00:48:53.809
I wanna say something.

859
00:48:53.892 --> 00:48:56.811
Go ahead. Say it.

860
00:49:02.776 --> 00:49:04.403
I wanna say it to them.

861
00:49:04.486 --> 00:49:06.446
Why don't you sit down
and I'll make you a drink?

862
00:49:06.738 --> 00:49:07.739
I have to tell them.

863
00:49:07.822 --> 00:49:09.324
-Elizabeth. no.
-Mom.

864
00:49:09.407 --> 00:49:10.826
I have to tell them
he's better than that.

865
00:49:10.909 --> 00:49:13.453
He's. he's better than
what they're saying.

866
00:49:13.536 --> 00:49:14.536
Goddamnit.

867
00:49:35.934 --> 00:49:37.853
It's okay.
Let's go inside.

868
00:52:21.933 --> 00:52:24.602
A Christmas miracle.

869
00:52:26.104 --> 00:52:30.150
Thank you.

870
00:52:34.529 --> 00:52:36.948
Hmm. Look at that.

871
00:52:37.782 --> 00:52:39.034
Hmm.

872
00:52:45.957 --> 00:52:49.044
You wanna pull up a chair?

873
00:52:49.127 --> 00:52:51.129
Don't see how you did it.

874
00:52:52.797 --> 00:52:55.633
Flabby. fat-headed creampuff.

875
00:53:01.514 --> 00:53:03.224
Just a little magic.

876
00:53:05.977 --> 00:53:07.604
I'll show ya.

877
00:53:07.687 --> 00:53:09.105
Give me your hand.

878
00:53:12.901 --> 00:53:14.653
You're the one
with the gun here.

879
00:53:14.736 --> 00:53:16.780
I don't know
what you're afraid of.

880
00:53:16.863 --> 00:53:20.534
I'm just a fat-headed creampuff.
remember?

881
00:53:20.617 --> 00:53:21.702
Look.

882
00:53:25.997 --> 00:53:27.582
That's all I got up my sleeve.

883
00:53:27.665 --> 00:53:28.875
Scout's honor.

884
00:53:29.876 --> 00:53:33.963
Now. I just need you to roll up
yours and make a fist.

885
00:53:49.646 --> 00:53:51.147
There you go.

886
00:54:05.286 --> 00:54:06.871
Okay.

887
00:54:08.164 --> 00:54:13.044
Now. pretend that
your wrist is your neck.

888
00:54:14.337 --> 00:54:16.590
I was a piss-poor Boy Scout.

889
00:54:16.673 --> 00:54:18.717
Never got past Second Class.

890
00:54:18.800 --> 00:54:21.887
I could build a fire
and push comes to shove.

891
00:54:21.970 --> 00:54:26.182
but I was real good at knots.

892
00:54:26.433 --> 00:54:27.892
Need your pen.

893
00:54:50.790 --> 00:54:52.751
Your airway's cut off.

894
00:54:53.043 --> 00:54:54.920
Struggling makes it worse.

895
00:54:55.003 --> 00:54:56.921
You won't last
more than a minute.

896
00:55:11.144 --> 00:55:13.146
Rope works better.

897
00:55:29.704 --> 00:55:32.749
John Wayne Gacy. Jr. I'm sorry?

898
00:55:32.832 --> 00:55:34.209
What's the spelling?

899
00:55:34.292 --> 00:55:36.003
It's G-A-C-E-Y.

900
00:55:36.086 --> 00:55:39.339
He's 36 years old.
Yes. Mr. Gacy is cooperating.

901
00:55:39.422 --> 00:55:41.216
What's Gacy's address?

902
00:55:41.299 --> 00:55:43.927
8213 West Summerdale.

903
00:55:44.010 --> 00:55:47.639
Information we received. uh.

904
00:55:48.807 --> 00:55:50.058
from our investigation.

905
00:55:50.141 --> 00:55:53.061
from other witnesses
led us to the crawlspace.

906
00:55:53.144 --> 00:55:54.771
Lieutenant.
do you feel in your own

907
00:55:54.854 --> 00:55:56.607
professional opinion that you
solved the disappearance

908
00:55:56.690 --> 00:55:58.274
of at least Piest boy?

909
00:55:58.608 --> 00:56:00.860
No.
I couldn't say that right now.

909
